OL,3,CChannel Island Catholic leaders react
OL,4,Cto Pope Francis' death
OL,6,FJersey's Bailiff, Sir Timothy Le Cocq,
OL,7,Fsays flags should fly at half-mast
OL,8,Funtil 8pm on Tuesday 22 April.
OL,10,FHe adds he is "saddened" to hear of
OL,11,Fthe passing of "a much-loved and
OL,12,Frespected figure".
OL,14,FCatholic Dean of Guernsey, the Very
OL,15,FReverand Canon Christopher Rutledge,
OL,16,Fsays the Pope had a love for the
OL,17,F"simplicity of life".
